# bad_subject
# ===========
# One Perl regular expression per line, matched against Subject.  A hit is a
# direct rejection, so every active expression should identify a campaign, not
# merely a topic or ordinary word.
#
# Exact recurring form with a numeric suffix:
# ^Exclusive campaign 2026 #[0-9]{4,8}$
#
# Literal square brackets must be escaped:
# ^\[ABUSE-CAMPAIGN-4711\]
#
# Two known variants followed by a 12-character hexadecimal reference:
# ^(?:Campaign Alpha|Campaign Beta) - ref [A-F0-9]{12}$
#
# Optional word and bounded whitespace:
# ^Offer(?: update)?\s{1,3}ID-[0-9]{6}$
#
# Case-insensitive matching is normally provided by Cleanfeed; do not repeat
# every upper/lowercase spelling.  Avoid generic words such as "free", "sale",
# "help", currencies, punctuation-only patterns, or file extensions.
